      • extractEmail

        public java.lang.String extractEmail(javax.json.JsonObject data)
        Extracts: email address. Input format: 
         TELECOM: [
        {
                TELECOM_SYSTEM: TELECOM_SYSTEM_EMAIL,
                TELECOM_SYSTEM_VALUE: "bob25mary@gmail.com"
        }
 ]

        This method will use the first TELECOM_SYSTEM=TELECOM_SYSTEM_EMAIL field inside the data source, if any.

        Specified by:

      • extractTrueNTHID

        public long extractTrueNTHID(javax.json.JsonObject data)
        Extracts: TrueNTH ID.

        Input format: 

         IDENTIFIER: [
         {
                IDENTIFIER_SYSTEM: IDENTIFIER_TRUENTH_SYSTEM,
                IDENTIFIER_VALUE: 9999
         },
         {
                IDENTIFIER_SYSTEM: IDENTIFIER_TRUENTH_SYSTEM_USERNAME,
                IDENTIFIER_VALUE: "username"
         }
 ]
        Input Example: 
         "identifier": [
       {
           "system": "http://us.truenth.org/identity-codes/TrueNTH-identity",
           "value": 10015
